dashboardItems.text: *Service monitoring*
*SERVICE AVAILABILITY AND STOCKOUT*
SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE

Key populations (KP) include men who have sex with men (MSM), sex workers, people who inject drugs, people in prisons and other closed settings, and trans and gender diverse people.  

Key populations, due to specific higher-risk behaviours, are at increased risk of HIV, viral hepatitis or STIs irrespective of the epidemic type or local context. Also, they often have legal and social issues related to their behaviours that increase their vulnerability to HIV.

A case can belong to more than one KP group and can leave or enter groups over time.
SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE
The gender category of ‘Other’ includes trans and gender diverse people who choose an identity other than male or female

*Probable route of transmission* and *Vertical Transmission*

Probable route of transmission includes categories of heterosexual sex, sex between men, unprotected intercourse during sex work, injecting drug use with unsterile equipment, nosocomial, vertical, other.  

The category of ‘other’ may include needle accidents, blood transfusion, blood products or organ/tissue donations, tattoos, piercings, circumcision, or acupuncture.

Probable route of transmission may only be collected where feasible and data security and confidentiality can be ensured.

Final outcome of PMTCT can be reported among HIV-exposed infants born within the past 12 months (or 24 months in breastfeeding settings)

dashboardItems.text: SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE
SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE
SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE

*MOR.1 AIDS mortality*

Total number of people who have died from AIDS-related causes per 100 000 population

*ART.2 Total attrition from ART*

Proportion of people living with HIV on ART at the end of the last reporting period and those newly initiating ART during the current reporting period who were not on ART at the end of the current reporting period

_Numerator_
Number of people living with HIV reported on ART at the end of the last reporting period *plus* Number of people living with HIV newly initiated on ART during the current reporting period *minus* Total number of people living with HIV on ART at the end of the current reporting period

_Denominator_
Number of people reported on ART at the end of the last reporting period *plus* those newly initiated on ART during the current reporting period

This will calculate the total number of individuals who are classified as having died, stopped treatment and/or been lost to follow-up by the end of the current period.

The recommended threshold for designation of people living with HIV on ART as lost to followup is 28 days after the last missed appointment or last ARV refill, to account for DSD ART.  See chapter 3 of WHO's 'Consolidated guidelines on person-centred HIV strategic information' for additional information.

*ART.1 People living with HIV on ART* 
_Cumulative Cases_ 

Proportion of people on ART among all people living with HIV

*NOTE*
Cases under _PLHIV on ART_ have a positive test and were initiated on ART at least once.
SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE

*ART retention and treatment status*

The information reported referred to the last visit and only PLHIV are included


The gender category of ‘Other’ includes trans and gender diverse people who choose an identity other than male or female

*HTS.4 Linkage to ART*

Proportion of people newly diagnosed with HIV initiated on ART

_Numerator_
Newly diagnosed with HIV and started ART during the reporting period


_Denominator_
Newly diagnosed with HIV during the reporting period




*ART.5 Late ART initiation*

_Numerator_
Number of people living with HIV initiating ART during the reporting period with a baseline CD4 count of <200 cells/mm3


_Denominator_
Number of people living with HIV initiating ART during the reporting period who have a baseline CD4 cell count
SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE

*ART.6 Viral load testing coverage*
Proportion of people living with HIV on ART (for at least six months) with viral load test results

_Numerator_
Number of people living with HIV on ART with at least one routine VL test result during the reporting period

_Denominator_
Number of people living with HIV on ART for at least six months


*ART.3 People living with HIV on ART who have suppressed viral load*
Proportion of people living with HIV on ART (for at least six months) who have virological suppression

_Numerator_
Number of people living with HIV on ART for at least six months and with at least one routine VL test result who have virological suppression (<1000 copies/mL) during the reporting period

_Denominator_
Number of people living with HIV on ART at least six months with at least one routine VL result in a medical or laboratory record during the reporting period, to monitor progress towards the third 95 target
SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE

*ART.7 Early viral load testing (at six months)*

Proportion of people living with HIV on ART who had a viral load result reviewed by six months after initiation of ART

_Numerator_
Number of people living with HIV on ART who were eligible for VL monitoring at six months after initiation of ART during the reporting period and who had a VL test performed and result reviewed by six months after ART initiation

_Denominator_
Number of people living with HIV on ART eligible for VL monitoring at six months after initiation of ART during the reporting period

*TB prevention treatment*

_TPT Initiation_ : Eligible PLHIV on ART who initiated TB preventive treatment, cumulative.

_TPT Completion_ : PLHIV on ART who completed a course of TB preventive treatment among those who initiated TPT, cumulative.

All indicators on this dashboard exclude cases marked "died" or "lost to follow up", but may include cases which stopped TPT treatment and later resumed treatment. 
PLHIV on ART are not eligible for TPT if they exhibit certain co-morbidities, including active hepatitis, chronic alcoholism and/or neuropathy

*TB screening and diagnostic cascade*
Screening and diagnostic cascade indicators are considered priority for high burden HIV/TB settings

*HIV CS CASCADE*


*HTS.1 PLHIV Who Know Their Status (%)*: Proportion of people living with HIV who know their HIV status (over estimated number of PLHIV)

*ART.1 PLHIV on ART (%)* : Proportion of people on ART among all people living with HIV

*ART.3 PLHIV Who have Suppressed VL (%)*: Proportion of people living with HIV on ART (for at least six months) who have virological suppression

*People Living With HIV*: Number of people living with HIV who have received their diagnosis and are still alive

*PLHIV tested for Viral Load*: PLHIV on ART for at least 6 months with at least one routine VL test result during the reporting period

*PLHIV virally suppressed*: PLHIV on ART for at least six months and last routine VL test result virologically suppressed (<1000 copies/mL1)

*DEFINITIONS:*
Closing balance = Opening balance + Received - Distributed - Redistributed - Discarded -->Automatically calculated indicator to count the remaining items at the end of the period
Stock on hand = physical stock count at the end of the period
Usable stock = Opening balance + received
Coverage time = Usable stock / Distributed + Discarded + Redistributed = no. of months

Stock discrepancy = Stock on hand - closing balance
If discrepancy = 0 and 9 --> Stock on hand = closing balance (green cell) - acceptable discrepancy -
If discrepancy < 0 --> closing balance > stock on hand (dark red cell)
If discrepancy > 9 --> closing balance < stock on hand (light red cell)

maps.description:
This visualisation is intended to facilitate the identification of population that has accesibility constraints to an HIV testing service.
Each point is an health facility which has been added a buffer of 5 km representing the accesibility to it.
A layer of population (the points in red) represent the estimated number of people living in that area (source: WorldPop / Google Earth Engine)
The health facility in blue are the ones offering the HIV testing service and with the cactchment area (5km) you can identify which population is covered or not by this service
